channel.title: Hey :D
channel.description:
hey,
Ok so ive been inactive on rsps communitys for a while, toke a break to concentrate on my own server/client :D so now im back im guna show u some work ive been doing, shields :D.
Ok so these were made for a quest ive added, but i cant decide which is the best, so please with no flame coz that sucks :P, tell me which you think is the best,
[IMG]http://i246.photobucket.com/albums/gg113/rs-kombatking/12-03-201023-05-55.png[/img]
Now this version isnt transparent, its quite a unique design, and the cross its self is pretty nice.
Ok on to version 2,
[IMG]http://i246.photobucket.com/albums/gg113/rs-kombatking/13-03-201003-41-36.png[/img]
Now this version is fully transparent, and the design is unlike any design ive done before :D
Ok rate and hate :) Gary

item.title: Hey :D
item.dc:creator: @gary1988 gary1988
item.description:
@gary1988 wrote:

[quote=“the elve age, post:9, topic:333209”]See, i told you to post it on mopar

Ontopic: I like the overall design better on 2nd model, but i like the 1st one more, if that makes any sense.

Add gold to them, (kind of like a sara shield)[/quote]

yeah, thanks ;), ill see what i can come up with

[quote=“dylan_0789, post:8, topic:333209”][quote author=CoonHunter link=topic=429625.msg3154766#msg3154766 date=1268933947]

Looks traced, Try using Prims.

Shield 1 is possible for Prim’s. Shield 2, would have been ALOT harder because of the shape because of how it is built.

@TOPIC - Yea, 2nd one looks alot better. The first one looks like a spirit shield to me for some reason. No, not saying you copied because i know that you know better Just saying the over-all shape to it, but dont worry ive done that a few times trying to make something
[/quote]
Actually, shield 2 would be easy with primitives, even the cross. You just need to know how to make it.

The shields are decent.[/quote]

I really need to start working more with prims tbh, as im still learning i like to prefect every aspect of modelling before i move on to a new style, if that makes sense

Mr Mopar:

There pretty good

Thanks man apriciate the feed back
